In any case, this is meant to be a /u/ fic first and foremost, so, the pairing, Erza x Zero.
Yes, Erza might as well be called overused when it comes to FT and pairings, but I do have a good reason for this one, other than her being one of the show's best characters.
When one stops to think about the two characters (after reading Zero's backstory novella, in specific), they might realize they could have a really good "two sides of the same coin" dynamic.
Both were born into poor childhoods, eventually ended up in some awful forced labor (Erza became a slave, Zero became a child whore) as children, both had a name given based on a color (Zero on the color of her eyes and Erza on the color of her hair), both tried and failed to escape only to suceed later, both were given the short side of the stick in the future by ending up somehow involved in a world-ending dark magic ritual, and both considered sacrifice to be the final answer to that issue.
What led them to be such different people despite having such awful pasts lies in the people around them. Erza was constantly surounded by people who cared and tried to help her:
Her mother only abandoned her in an attempt to give her a better life, she had loyal friends and a caring "grandpa" in the Tower, and after she left, she managed to find people who she could trust and confide in at the guild.
Meanwhile, Zero's mother didn't even care enough to give her a name, she was sold into prostitution, her only "friend" was only using her, after she killed her way out she was left alone and after years when she finally found someone she maybe trusted she was betrayed when she caught a plague, and then went on murdering random people before being captured and tortured to death.
They could very easily be played as "what the other would've became had they (not) have friends and loved ones", sort of a dark reflection. This sort of dynamic could easily be played for both conflict, pity and longing.
